Namasttay Shri Sanjay K Saini Ji And EveryOne,

[Sanjay Kumar Saini [sanjay.in@...] Sat 5/24/2014 18:39: ]
...... 2) no one can even shake a leaf without God's blessings, however our
own Karma will have their effect in direction of God's will..... 

[Kannan:]
No! This is absolutely untrue, the statement " No one can even shake a leaf
without God's Blessings". Because of erroneous notion spread like this,
people often roll over the conclusion that "All Evil present in this world
is due to God, as not even a leaf shakes without God's Will or Blessings".

Let me share the Truth. God is NOT a Control-Maniac. God is NOT a Fascist,
He is a Facilitator. He has given complete freedom to everyone including the
Evil Forces, to act the way they like, and subsequently face the
consequences. He has given human beings the necessary intellect which every
human has to cultivate through Vidya(Enlightenment), obtained through the
company of wise(Satsanga) and reading of Holy Sacred
Scriptures(Swaadhyaaya), and practicing the sermons thereof(Abhyaasa). Such
Corrected Intellect(Sanskaarita Buddhi) alone will be one's best friend and
guide one to decide wisely, the relevant course of action to be undertaken,
and thus enabling one to undertake the most apt act(Kartavyam), and thereby
attain heaven, peace, bliss, and happiness and growth(Jeevan-mukti).

If one is not going to cultivate one's intellect, and one sells it off to
The Evil, by daily brainwash of Television Watching(Television is the weapon
of the Evil to capture and destroy the intellectual growth. It is a hypnotic
device which will make one to do things without even knowing it), and
thereby if one becomes a Blind-Folded-Fanatic-Hero-Worshipper, and acts
foolishly, then God is not going to come and protect, no matter how many
bells you bang in the temple and pilgrimages.

This is because God has already given one the protection weapon or device
called "Buddhi' or "Intellect", which one regularly needs to sharpen like a
sword, otherwise it will rust out. If despite using all intellect, if The
Evil tortures a righteous person, then God surely runs in a fraction of a
second for help, even without calling him. I know My God. He is very Sweet,
very Lovable. He is a Strict Father and a Compassionate Mother, a True
friend, a wise Guru. I Love Him. There is really no suffering in life, if
one sharpens one's intellect by the ways I mentioned above.

With Kind Regards,
Kannan





